                     "topFinding":  "First deep bar-raise to look past the green dashboard into the project\u0027s own metadata. The game is healthy (pipeline reconciles at v0.99.15, worktree clean, no-accuracy/no-agency honored, live save round-trips) but the scaffolding has drifted to the pre-v0.98.5 2D world: the .project-context.json critical-files list points 7 of 9 entries at deleted files, the HTBH hazard catalog still enforces dual-path/path-extends on missing files, the scheduled tasks are phantom/misclassified, and the bar-raise routine silently produced no report for 06-26/-27/-28 (this run is the catch-up). The carryover engineering finding sharpens: the crowd3d MultiMesh renderer is built but unwired, so the live per-Node FBX path holds the full game to 34 fps at 2000 and 22 at 3000 enemies, under the S-34 ceiling. No hard-rule breach, so no BLOCK; verdict is in-progress with the longest action list in this project\u0027s review history.",
